<item>
            <title>[LU-13359] change lfs quota --pool to print used based only on OSTs from the pool</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13359</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/35615&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/35615&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&quot;lfs quota --pool&quot; shows correct soft/hard limit and grace time. However used is still the same with used without --pool option, i.e. it prints used for all OSTs in a system. print_obd_quota should be changed to take into account only OSTs from appropriate quota pool. I would like to do this in a separate ticket to make 35615 as small as possible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
